messages.title: How Safe Is YOUR Home?
messages.content: Expect many more developments with 500+ housing developments in all areas of Woking. 6,000+ high-density new homes to be crammed into the town involving the grab of recreation grounds, athletic tracks, and houses with long gardens.

keyPolicies.policyDescription: UKIP will insist councils hold binding local referenda for all major developments. Opposes Green Belt development.

issues.immigration: To house the 2.56 million immigrants that arrived since Conservatives took office in 2010.

housing.content: Expect many more developments with 500+ housing developments in all areas of Woking.

leaflet.additionalNotes: The leaflet focuses on concerns regarding housing development and immigration, suggesting a significant increase in housing development pressure due to population growth. It emphasizes the need for local referenda on major developments.
